      • getMonitoringThreshold

        int getMonitoringThreshold()
        Gets the monitoring threshold. Monitoring the build engine will cause the engine to be in a warning state if it does not contact the repository within the threshold.

        Note: In order to retrieve this the fetch of the engine must have included the PROPERTY_PROPERTIES.

        Returns:
        The monitoring threshold in minutes.

      • setMonitoringThreshold

        void setMonitoringThreshold(int thresholdMinutes)
        Sets the monitoring threshold. A value less than 1 disables monitoring. Monitoring the build engine will cause the engine to be in a warning state if it does not contact the repository within the threshold.
        Parameters:
        thresholdMinutes - The monitoring threshold in minutes.

      • isThresholdMonitoringEnabled

        boolean isThresholdMonitoringEnabled()
        Indicates if the engine is participating in threshold monitoring.

        Note: In order to retrieve this the fetch of the engine must have included the PROPERTY_PROPERTIES.

        Returns:
        true if the engine is participating in threshold monitoring.

      • copyEngine

        IBuildEngine copyEngine()
        Make a copy of this engine.
        Returns:
        The new build engine. It is a working copy and has not been saved. The origin is not set. The new copy has a different UUID than the original. The new copy has a clear history. The remainder of the contents are equal to the original.
        Since:
        0.8

      • initializeConfiguration

        void initializeConfiguration(IBuildConfigurationElement element)
        Initialize the build engine from the given configuration element. The element is added to the engine after existing configuration elements. In addition, the generic properties declared in the element's extension are copied into the build engine.

        If an element with the same id is already present in the engine, it is overwritten at its current position.

        This method may be called more than once with different configuration elements.

        Parameters:
        element - The configuration element to initialize the engine with.
        Since:
        0.8

      • initializeConfiguration

        void initializeConfiguration(IBuildEngineTemplate template)
        Initialize the build engine from the given template. The configuration elements specified by the template are copied into the engine. In addition, the generic properties declared in the template's extension are copied into the build engine. Any existing elements in the engine are overwritten by template elements with the same id. Likewise, any existing generic properties will be overwritten by template properties with the same name.

        This method may be called more than once with different templates.

        Parameters:
        template - The template to initialize the engine with.
        Since:
        0.8
